subSubSection.paragraph:
Abdomen. Body segments with some dorsal and ventral setae not more than 80 µm long; segments I–VII with 3 pairs of lateral setae 68–120 µm long; segment VIII with 1 pair lateral setae, segment IX without lateral setae. Procercus dark brown, 32–44 µm long, 28–40 µm wide, with 7–9 anal setae 560–608 µm long and 2 short and thin lateral setae (
Fig. 17
). Supraanal setae 200–336 µm long. Posterior parapods 400–448 µm long, 112–128 µm wide, in basal part ventral with pair of hair-like setae 124–160 µm long. Anal tubules cone-shaped, subequal in size 160– 208 µm long.
